ontent/uploads/2021/03/Granite-Design-AUX-strap-on-botte-Cage-kit-review-cyclingtips-4.jpg\" data-link=\"https://cyclingtips.com/?attachment_id=492195\" class=\"wp-image-492195\" srcset=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Granite-Design-AUX-strap-on-botte-Cage-kit-review-cyclingtips-4-1340x754.jpg 1340w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Granite-Design-AUX-strap-on-botte-Cage-kit-review-cyclingtips-4-650x366.jpg 650w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Granite-Design-AUX-strap-on-botte-Cage-kit-review-cyclingtips-4-190x107.jpg 190w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Granite-Design-AUX-strap-on-botte-Cage-kit-review-cyclingtips-4-1080x608.jpg 1080w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Granite-Design-AUX-strap-on-botte-Cage-kit-review-cyclingtips-4-16x9.jpg 16w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Granite-Design-AUX-strap-on-botte-Cage-kit-review-cyclingtips-4.jpg 1920w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1340px) 100vw, 1340px\" /><figcaption class=\"blocks-gallery-item__caption\">This rubber pad sits between the cage and the tube it&#8217;s being strapped to. </figcaption></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1340\" height=\"754\" src=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Granite-Design-AUX-strap-on-botte-Cage-kit-review-cyclingtips-5-1340x754.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"492198\" data-full-url=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Granite-Design-AUX-strap-on-botte-Cage-kit-review-cyclingtips-5.jpg\" data-link=\"https://cyclingtips.com/?attachment_id=492198\" class=\"wp-image-492198\" srcset=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Granite-Design-AUX-strap-on-botte-Cage-kit-review-cyclingtips-5-1340x754.jpg 1340w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Granite-Design-AUX-strap-on-botte-Cage-kit-review-cyclingtips-5-650x366.jpg 650w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Granite-Design-AUX-strap-on-botte-Cage-kit-review-cyclingtips-5-190x107.jpg 190w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Granite-Design-AUX-strap-on-botte-Cage-kit-review-cyclingtips-5-1080x608.jpg 1080w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Granite-Design-AUX-strap-on-botte-Cage-kit-review-cyclingtips-5-16x9.jpg 16w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Granite-Design-AUX-strap-on-botte-Cage-kit-review-cyclingtips-5.jpg 1920w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1340px) 100vw, 1340px\" /><figcaption class=\"blocks-gallery-item__caption\">Mounting the Aux cage is simple and doesn&#8217;t require tools (although some scissors may be needed for the excess strap length).</figcaption></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1340\" height=\"754\" src=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Granite-Design-AUX-strap-on-botte-Cage-kit-review-cyclingtips-6-1340x754.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"492201\" data-full-url=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Granite-Design-AUX-strap-on-botte-Cage-kit-review-cyclingtips-6.jpg\" data-link=\"https://cyclingtips.com/?attachment_id=492201\" class=\"wp-image-492201\" srcset=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Granite-Design-AUX-strap-on-botte-Cage-kit-review-cyclingtips-6-1340x754.jpg 1340w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Granite-Design-AUX-strap-on-botte-Cage-kit-review-cyclingtips-6-650x366.jpg 650w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Granite-Design-AUX-strap-on-botte-Cage-kit-review-cyclingtips-6-190x107.jpg 190w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Granite-Design-AUX-strap-on-botte-Cage-kit-review-cyclingtips-6-1080x608.jpg 1080w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Granite-Design-AUX-strap-on-botte-Cage-kit-review-cyclingtips-6-16x9.jpg 16w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Granite-Design-AUX-strap-on-botte-Cage-kit-review-cyclingtips-6.jpg 1920w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1340px) 100vw, 1340px\" /><figcaption class=\"blocks-gallery-item__caption\">Often the rubber pad will sit beneath the strap loops to prevent paint damage, but I&#8217;d say it&#8217;s still best to tape up the tube before. </figcaption></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1340\" height=\"754\" src=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Granite-Design-AUX-strap-on-botte-Cage-kit-review-cyclingtips-7-1340x754.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"492204\" data-full-url=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Granite-Design-AUX-strap-on-botte-Cage-kit-review-cyclingtips-7.jpg\" data-link=\"https://cyclingtips.com/?attachment_id=492204\" class=\"wp-image-492204\" srcset=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Granite-Design-AUX-strap-on-botte-Cage-kit-review-cyclingtips-7-1340x754.jpg 1340w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Granite-Design-AUX-strap-on-botte-Cage-kit-review-cyclingtips-7-650x366.jpg 650w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Granite-Design-AUX-strap-on-botte-Cage-kit-review-cyclingtips-7-190x107.jpg 190w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Granite-Design-AUX-strap-on-botte-Cage-kit-review-cyclingtips-7-1080x608.jpg 1080w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Granite-Design-AUX-strap-on-botte-Cage-kit-review-cyclingtips-7-16x9.jpg 16w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Granite-Design-AUX-strap-on-botte-Cage-kit-review-cyclingtips-7.jpg 1920w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1340px) 100vw, 1340px\" /><figcaption class=\"blocks-gallery-item__caption\">Snip to length. The straps don&#8217;t show any signs of fraying once cut.</figcaption></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1340\" height=\"754\" src=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Granite-Design-AUX-strap-on-botte-Cage-kit-review-cyclingtips-9-1340x754.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"492207\" data-full-url=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Granite-Design-AUX-strap-on-botte-Cage-kit-review-cyclingtips-9.jpg\" data-link=\"https://cyclingtips.com/?attachment_id=492207\" class=\"wp-image-492207\" srcset=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Granite-Design-AUX-strap-on-botte-Cage-kit-review-cyclingtips-9-1340x754.jpg 1340w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Granite-Design-AUX-strap-on-botte-Cage-kit-review-cyclingtips-9-650x366.jpg 650w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Granite-Design-AUX-strap-on-botte-Cage-kit-review-cyclingtips-9-190x107.jpg 190w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Granite-Design-AUX-strap-on-botte-Cage-kit-review-cyclingtips-9-1080x608.jpg 1080w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Granite-Design-AUX-strap-on-botte-Cage-kit-review-cyclingtips-9-16x9.jpg 16w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Granite-Design-AUX-strap-on-botte-Cage-kit-review-cyclingtips-9.jpg 1920w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1340px) 100vw, 1340px\" /><figcaption class=\"blocks-gallery-item__caption\">The cage itself is competitively low-weight while offering a secure hold. </figcaption></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1340\" height=\"754\" src=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Granite-Design-AUX-strap-on-botte-Cage-kit-review-cyclingtips-10-1340x754.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"492208\" data-full-url=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Granite-Design-AUX-strap-on-botte-Cage-kit-review-cyclingtips-10.jpg\" data-link=\"https://cyclingtips.com/?attachment_id=492208\" class=\"wp-image-492208\" srcset=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Granite-Design-AUX-strap-on-botte-Cage-kit-review-cyclingtips-10-1340x754.jpg 1340w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Granite-Design-AUX-strap-on-botte-Cage-kit-review-cyclingtips-10-650x366.jpg 650w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Granite-Design-AUX-strap-on-botte-Cage-kit-review-cyclingtips-10-190x107.jpg 190w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Granite-Design-AUX-strap-on-botte-Cage-kit-review-cyclingtips-10-1080x608.jpg 1080w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Granite-Design-AUX-strap-on-botte-Cage-kit-review-cyclingtips-10-16x9.jpg 16w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Granite-Design-AUX-strap-on-botte-Cage-kit-review-cyclingtips-10.jpg 1920w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1340px) 100vw, 1340px\" /><figcaption class=\"blocks-gallery-item__caption\">Unfortunately there&#8217;s no good way of looping in the excess strap length and so it must be cut to length.</figcaption></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1340\" height=\"754\" src=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Granite-Design-AUX-strap-on-botte-Cage-kit-review-cyclingtips-12-1340x754.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"492213\" data-full-url=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Granite-Design-AUX-strap-on-botte-Cage-kit-review-cyclingtips-12.jpg\" data-link=\"https://cyclingtips.com/?attachment_id=492213\" class=\"wp-image-492213\" srcset=\"https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Granite-Design-AUX-strap-on-botte-Cage-kit-review-cyclingtips-12-1340x754.jpg 1340w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Granite-Design-AUX-strap-on-botte-Cage-kit-review-cyclingtips-12-650x366.jpg 650w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Granite-Design-AUX-strap-on-botte-Cage-kit-review-cyclingtips-12-190x107.jpg 190w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Granite-Design-AUX-strap-on-botte-Cage-kit-review-cyclingtips-12-1080x608.jpg 1080w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Granite-Design-AUX-strap-on-botte-Cage-kit-review-cyclingtips-12-16x9.jpg 16w, https://cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Granite-Design-AUX-strap-on-botte-Cage-kit-review-cyclingtips-12.jpg 1920w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1340px) 100vw, 1340px\" /><figcaption class=\"blocks-gallery-item__caption\">The Aux cage and Strap kit allow you to mount a bottle cage to just about anywhere, but you&#8217;ll still want to consider if the placement is practical. Personally I see this as being most useful for fork-mounted carrying or on frames that lack mounts in commonly-used spots.</figcaption></figure></li></ul></figure>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://cyclingtips.com/2021/03/granite-design-aux-bottle-cage-review/\">Spotlight: Granite Design Aux bottle cage review</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://cyclingtips.com\">CyclingTips</a>.</p>","author":"Dave Rome","siteTitle":"CyclingTips","siteHash":"30feca30fb3902119bf2da6559e7337232527b61c9abe0a00f5d7543c6aa6c84","entryHash":"d6dbd229b680c1f98c7dbf443ec050c0884ab05c931dc4b3393a073454663132","category":"Cycling"}